verses.plain: Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest between the cherubims, shine forth.

tokens.t: Give ear, O Shepherd of Israel, thou that leadest Joseph like a flock; thou that dwellest
the cherubims, shine forth.

verses.plain: Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come and save us.

tokens.t: Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up thy strength, and come
save us.

verses.plain: Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

tokens.t: Turn us again, O God, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

verses.plain: O LORD God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?

tokens.t: O
God of hosts, how long wilt thou be angry against the prayer of thy people?

verses.plain: Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.

tokens.t: Thou feedest them with the bread of tears; and givest them tears to drink in great measure.

verses.plain: Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.

tokens.t: Thou makest us a strife unto our neighbours: and our enemies laugh among themselves.

verses.plain: Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

tokens.t: Turn us again, O God of hosts, and cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

verses.plain: Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.

tokens.t: Thou hast brought a vine out of Egypt: thou hast cast out the heathen, and planted it.

verses.plain: Thou preparedst room before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.

tokens.t: Thou preparedst
before it, and didst cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.

verses.plain: The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars.

tokens.t: The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof
the goodly cedars.

verses.plain: She sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.

tokens.t: She sent out her boughs unto the sea, and her branches unto the river.

verses.plain: Why hast thou then broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?

tokens.t: Why hast thou
broken down her hedges, so that all they which pass by the way do pluck her?

verses.plain: The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.

tokens.t: The boar out of the wood doth waste it, and the wild beast of the field doth devour it.

verses.plain: Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;

tokens.t: Return, we beseech thee, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;

verses.plain: And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch that thou madest strong for thyself.

tokens.t: And the vineyard which thy right hand hath planted, and the branch
thou madest strong for thyself.

verses.plain: It is burned with fire, it is cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.

tokens.t: burned with fire,
cut down: they perish at the rebuke of thy countenance.

verses.plain: Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man whom thou madest strong for thyself.

tokens.t: Let thy hand be upon the man of thy right hand, upon the son of man
thou madest strong for thyself.

verses.plain: So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.

tokens.t: So will not we go back from thee: quicken us, and we will call upon thy name.

verses.plain: Turn us again, O LORD God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.

tokens.t: Turn us again, O
God of hosts, cause thy face to shine; and we shall be saved.
